news.title: Mohali: Drone survey done at Khaspur village
news.para: A flagship project was initiated by the Punjab government under Mera Ghar Mere Naam, called Swamitwa scheme, which aims to give ownership rights to properties built within the lal dora (red line), said Rajesh Tripathi, director land records.

news.title: Bhubaneswar civic body signs MoU for survey to give slum dwellers land rights
news.para: The survey called Urban Slum Household Area (USHA) will be conducted in 436 slums under the state government’s Jaga Mission to provide land rights to slum dwellers.

news.title: Ludhiana: Six-member panel to probe irregularities in PMAY scheme
news.para: Officials have been given 15 days’ time to submit the inquiry report. During a previous inquiry conducted at the level of the additional commissioner, the employee was held guilty and investigation was recommended.

news.title: Eight houses built under PMAY 'missing' in Satna district
news.para: Though the ‘missing houses’ date back to 2017-18, sources said they were never built but shown as complete on papers in Rahikwara panchayat of Satna district.

news.title: Noida: Rehabilitation site too far, villagers protest at YEIDA office
news.para: The villagers said the new R&R site is 30km away from the Jewar airport project site and it would also be devoid of local markets and other facilities.

news.title: DGGI unearths GST evasion in real estate sector in Kerala
news.para: "The detection in this regard stands at Rs 50.84 crore and a recovery of Rs 26.01 crore has been made,” the statement said.

news.title: Sebi extends time till Nov 9 to auction properties of Saradha Group of companies
news.para: The regulator will auction as many as 69 properties of Saradha Group of Companies for a reserve price of Rs 30 crore. The move is part of Sebi's efforts to recover money raised by the company from public through illicit schemes.

news.title: Sebi to auction properties of Bishal Group of companies on Nov 30 to recover money
news.para: The 10 properties put on the block are vacant lands and a residential property located in West Bengal. Total reserve price of these properties is pegged at Rs 14.4 crore, the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Sebi) said in a notice.

news.title: Foreign funds raise bets on retail realty amid higher rental incomes
news.para: Retail accounted for 14% of the total investments in commercial real estate assets in the first nine months of 2022, up from 8% in the year 2021, according to an analysis by global consultancy firm Vestian. Share of retail in total investments in 2018 and 2019 were 4% and 3%, respectively, it said.

news.title: Fewer working days in October affect property registrations in Maharashtra
news.para: Data shared by the property registration department showed that 1.62 lakh properties were registered and Rs3,211.5 crore collected this month (till 27th) .

news.title: Noida authority allows registration of 300 units at Wave Mega City Centre
news.para: Earlier this year, Wave Megacity Centre Private Limited was directed to pay around Rs 90 crore in dues -- Rs 56 crore in principal amount and Rs 34 crore for its projects in sectors 25A and 32.

news.title: Builder luring with e-way link liable to refund if it's not ready, says NCDRC
news.para: Now the NCDRC has warned that such builders will have to refund money to homebuyers if Metro or road link is not constructed by the authorities during the promised time-frame.

news.title: Mumbai: Private builders invited to revive 500 'dead' slum redevelopment projects
news.para: According to SRA officials, applications from private builders to empanel them will be scrutinised, and they will be empanelled in A, B & C categories to complete dead projects which are stuck since as far back as 2005.

news.title: France's Saint-Gobain sees energy, raw materials soaring this year
news.para: Saint-Gobain quarterly revenue rose 19.6% year-on-year to 12.9 billion euros, beating the 12.7 billion euros average estimate from a company-provided consensus, thanks to double-digit organic growth in all segments, driven in particular by high performance solutions, Asia-Pacific and North America.

news.title: Indore: Probe ordered into plot allotment in toy cluster
news.para: According to the official sources, there are allegations of allotting plots in toy clusters by sidelining the set rules of MP state industrial land and building management rules and MP MSME Development Policy 2021.
